1
00:00:17.851 --> 00:00:21.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[indistinct conversation]

2
00:00:51.385 --> 00:00:54.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[indistinct conversation]

3
00:01:01.019 --> 00:01:04.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Excuse me, can you tell me
where I can find the supervisor?

4
00:01:04.982 --> 00:01:06.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Over there.
-Thank you.

5
00:01:16.201 --> 00:01:19.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your authorization
and licenses, please?

6
00:01:21.164 --> 00:01:25.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Level 6 in Thermodynamics
<i>and</i> Quantum Fusion.

7
00:01:25.460 --> 00:01:29.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, Janeway, I'm impressed.
-Thank you, sir.

8
00:01:29.756 --> 00:01:32.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, if you could just manage
to report to your shift on time.

9
00:01:32.467 --> 00:01:34.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry. I boarded
the wrong transport.

10
00:01:34.511 --> 00:01:37.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I ended up at the Atmosphere
Filtration Facility.

11
00:01:37.514 --> 00:01:39.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're always looking
for skilled workers.

12
00:01:39.349 --> 00:01:41.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm surprised
they didn't offer you a job.

13
00:01:41.226 --> 00:01:42.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I promise I won't be late again.

14
00:01:42.686 --> 00:01:45.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, it's easy to get disoriented
when you're new here.

15
00:01:45.104 --> 00:01:48.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been in this city all my life,
and I still get lost on occasion.

16
00:01:48.692 --> 00:01:51.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, you'll be monitoring
the primary reactor coils.

17
00:01:51.737 --> 00:01:53.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They process more
than 8,000 metric...

18
00:01:53.405 --> 00:01:55.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
8,000 metric tons
of tylium per second

19
00:01:55.532 --> 00:01:57.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
at 94 percent thermal efficiency.

20
00:01:59.036 --> 00:02:01.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I memorized the specifications.

21
00:02:01.330 --> 00:02:03.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let me know
if there's anything you need.

22
00:02:03.582 --> 00:02:06.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll find we like
to keep our workforce happy.

23
00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:10.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can already tell it's going to be
much better than my last job.

24
00:04:18.467 --> 00:04:20.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The specifications you asked for.

25
00:04:20.302 --> 00:04:21.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

26
00:04:38.361 --> 00:04:39.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[alarm sounds]

27
00:04:39.863 --> 00:04:42.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[Computer]
Input Error 415.

28
00:04:43.784 --> 00:04:47.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Command Code Violation 2308.

29
00:04:47.788 --> 00:04:49.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[alarm continues]

30
00:04:49.581 --> 00:04:51.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Come on,
shut off that damn alarm,

31
00:04:51.666 --> 00:04:54.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
and I promise I'll never
violate you again.

32
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:56.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[alarm stops]

33
00:04:56.254 --> 00:04:58.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You almost started
a core overload.

34
00:04:58.590 --> 00:04:59.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I would have corrected it.

35
00:04:59.925 --> 00:05:03.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, I'm sorry for interrupting, then.
And for eavesdropping.

36
00:05:03.845 --> 00:05:06.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I overheard you talking
to your console.

37
00:05:06.515 --> 00:05:09.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-It's an old habit.
-Does it work?

38
00:05:09.226 --> 00:05:13.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'm not sure this control panel and I
speak the same language yet.

39
00:05:13.230 --> 00:05:16.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, if you need an interpreter...
Jaffen.

40
00:05:17.108 --> 00:05:18.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kathryn.

41
00:05:18.235 --> 00:05:19.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I work just down there.

42
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:20.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's good to know.

43
00:05:20.987 --> 00:05:23.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Seven] This station doesn't
require two operators.

44
00:05:24.699 --> 00:05:27.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-I don't think we've met. I'm...
-Employee 1326.

45
00:05:27.744 --> 00:05:30.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And you're Employee 8584.

46
00:05:30.455 --> 00:05:31.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Since you're new here,

47
00:05:31.706 --> 00:05:33.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you may not be fully familiar
with the labor protocols,

48
00:05:33.834 --> 00:05:35.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but you should be aware

49
00:05:35.085 --> 00:05:36.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that fraternizing is not
permitted during work hours.

50
00:05:36.753 --> 00:05:38.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And do you have a number
or maybe a name?

51
00:05:39.047 --> 00:05:40.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Annika Hansen.

52
00:05:40.799 --> 00:05:42.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And what exactly is
your position here?

53
00:05:42.968 --> 00:05:44.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm the new Efficiency Monitor.

54
00:05:44.636 --> 00:05:47.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, I, uh, didn't know
they'd hired one.

55
00:05:47.597 --> 00:05:50.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now that you do, I suggest
you return to your station.

56
00:05:50.392 --> 00:05:51.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Janeway]
We weren't fraternizing.

57
00:05:51.810 --> 00:05:54.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He was just helping me
correct an input error.

58
00:05:54.104 --> 00:05:55.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're almost finished.

59
00:05:55.939 --> 00:05:58.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Do it quickly.
-Yes, ma'am.

60
00:05:59.985 --> 00:06:01.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought we were fraternizing.

61
00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:03.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[laughs quietly]

62
00:06:06.074 --> 00:06:07.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Maybe we could get
acquainted after work.

63
00:06:08.076 --> 00:06:10.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Uh, there is a little place
some of us like to go to.

64
00:06:10.787 --> 00:06:12.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-We could get a meal.
-I can't.

65
00:06:12.998 --> 00:06:15.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You need to talk to someone
besides your console.

66
00:06:15.667 --> 00:06:19.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I appreciate the offer,
but with this new job,

67
00:06:19.629 --> 00:06:21.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't really have time
to socialize.

68
00:06:21.798 --> 00:06:22.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

69
00:06:33.518 --> 00:06:37.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're always looking for laborers
at the Power Distribution Plant.

70
00:06:37.522 --> 00:06:41.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I had a job there once.
Didn't like it much.

71
00:06:41.192 --> 00:06:45.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Odd.
They treat their employees well.

72
00:06:45.822 --> 00:06:47.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How long were you there?

73
00:06:47.532 --> 00:06:48.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, a while.

74
00:06:48.909 --> 00:06:52.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would be very simple
for me to find out.

75
00:06:52.203 --> 00:06:53.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A day.

76
00:06:53.330 --> 00:06:55.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A day?

77
00:06:55.665 --> 00:06:58.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Half a day, actually,
give or take an hour.

78
00:06:59.044 --> 00:07:01.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not what I'd call an illustrious career.

79
00:07:02.047 --> 00:07:06.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't belong behind a console
pushing buttons.

80
00:07:06.384 --> 00:07:11.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But when I heard some of the workers
talking about your place,

81
00:07:11.139 --> 00:07:13.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I knew I had to get a job here.

82
00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:16.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You were terminated, weren't you?

83
00:07:16.186 --> 00:07:17.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

84
00:07:17.312 --> 00:07:21.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, that's quite an accomplishment
during a labor shortage.

85
00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:22.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What happened?

86
00:07:22.901 --> 00:07:24.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, it's a long story.

87
00:07:25.070 --> 00:07:27.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I like a long story.

88
00:07:27.864 --> 00:07:31.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I had a disagreement with
the new Efficiency Monitor.

89
00:07:31.493 --> 00:07:33.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She didn't think
my work was very...

90
00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:35.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Efficient?
-Exactly.

91
00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:37.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then why should I hire you?

92
00:07:37.374 --> 00:07:42.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, there's my natural charm
and personality.

93
00:07:42.087 --> 00:07:44.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They'd be a real asset
around a place like this,

94
00:07:44.089 --> 00:07:46.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
where you're trying
to attract patrons.

95
00:07:46.091 --> 00:07:48.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, look at you.

96
00:07:48.093 --> 00:07:50.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You haven't been able
to tear yourself away from me.

97
00:07:50.095 --> 00:07:52.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no one else here.

98
00:07:55.976 --> 00:07:57.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

99
00:07:58.269 --> 00:07:59.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please.

100
00:07:59.896 --> 00:08:02.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I really need the work.

101
00:08:04.526 --> 00:08:07.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'd better clean those tables
over there.

102
00:08:07.153 --> 00:08:09.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This place is going to be
filled with hungry workers

103
00:08:09.364 --> 00:08:10.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
as soon as the next shift ends.

104
00:08:11.032 --> 00:08:12.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You won't regret this.

105
00:08:12.951 --> 00:08:15.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'm certain I will.

106
00:08:24.796 --> 00:08:27.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[indistinct conversation, laughter]

107
00:08:27.507 --> 00:08:29.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Jaffen]
...all of them about my father,

108
00:08:29.092 --> 00:08:31.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and he couldn't understand
why I wasn't insulted.

109
00:08:31.594 --> 00:08:34.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Finally, I just had to tell him:
I'm Norvalian.

110
00:08:34.180 --> 00:08:35.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't have a father.

111
00:08:35.724 --> 00:08:38.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughter]

112
00:08:38.184 --> 00:08:40.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[hearty laughter]

113
00:08:40.895 --> 00:08:42.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It wasn't that funny, Tuvok.

114
00:08:42.814 --> 00:08:45.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chortling]
On the contrary.

115
00:08:45.483 --> 00:08:48.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The man was ignorant of how
your species procreates.

116
00:08:48.903 --> 00:08:49.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs]

117
00:08:50.030 --> 00:08:54.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
His attempt to disparage you
ultimately humiliated him.

118
00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:55.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs]

119
00:08:55.827 --> 00:08:57.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Irony is often a source of humor.

120
00:08:57.704 --> 00:09:00.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, well, when you explain it
like that, uh...

121
00:09:00.707 --> 00:09:02.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
it's not funny at all.

122
00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:04.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I also have some
humorous anecdotes to share.

123
00:09:04.919 --> 00:09:06.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll look forward to hearing them.

124
00:09:07.714 --> 00:09:10.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you didn't
have time to socialize.

125
00:09:10.508 --> 00:09:11.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not socializing.

126
00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:14.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm reviewing these manuals
and having something to eat.

127
00:09:14.554 --> 00:09:16.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I recommend
the Latara broth

128
00:09:16.264 --> 00:09:18.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and the section
on thermal coefficients.

129
00:09:18.099 --> 00:09:20.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll join you.
-Really, I'm very, very busy.

130
00:09:20.685 --> 00:09:24.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, not to socialize. To, uh,
help you review the manuals.

131
00:09:25.065 --> 00:09:27.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs gently]

132
00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:28.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man]
How was your first day?

133
00:09:28.735 --> 00:09:30.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[sighs heavily]
Here you are.

134
00:09:30.653 --> 00:09:32.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Compliments of the proprietress.

135
00:09:33.031 --> 00:09:34.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Umali]
Tom.

136
00:09:34.657 --> 00:09:36.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, I'll be right back.

137
00:09:38.495 --> 00:09:41.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The proprietress
doesn't give away drinks.

138
00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:43.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I'm just creating
customer loyalty.

139
00:09:43.875 --> 00:09:47.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've been creating loyalty all night
with those two women.

140
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:49.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I suggest you attend
to the other tables.

141
00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:50.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, ma'am.

142
00:09:53.676 --> 00:09:56.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Here you are.
-Thank you. Looks great.

143
00:10:11.736 --> 00:10:14.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't believe
I let you keep me out this late.

144
00:10:14.572 --> 00:10:16.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I thought it was
my responsibility

145
00:10:16.282 --> 00:10:17.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to help you study those manuals.

146
00:10:18.034 --> 00:10:20.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[laughing] Of course.
-And now that I have,

147
00:10:20.411 --> 00:10:22.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you should be less likely
to overload the core.

148
00:10:22.247 --> 00:10:23.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

149
00:10:26.751 --> 00:10:28.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, with all this
fascinating discussion

150
00:10:29.045 --> 00:10:30.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
about thermal coefficients,

151
00:10:30.338 --> 00:10:32.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you never told me where you're from.

152
00:10:32.215 --> 00:10:34.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A planet called Earth.

153
00:10:34.092 --> 00:10:35.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never heard of it.

154
00:10:35.718 --> 00:10:38.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh, a<i> long</i> way from here.
-What's it like?

155
00:10:38.555 --> 00:10:42.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Overpopulated, polluted,
very little work.

156
00:10:42.809 --> 00:10:44.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It sounds like my homeworld.

157
00:10:44.894 --> 00:10:46.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Guess we're both
lucky to be here.

158
00:10:46.813 --> 00:10:49.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's nice to be in a place where
different species get along so well.

159
00:10:49.691 --> 00:10:51.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, so, you admit we're getting along.

160
00:10:51.192 --> 00:10:54.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was speaking
in a broader cultural context.

161
00:10:54.529 --> 00:10:55.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see.

162
00:10:56.072 --> 00:10:58.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a lot of violence
where I come from.

163
00:10:59.075 --> 00:11:00.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's too bad.

164
00:11:01.035 --> 00:11:02.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man]
It's getting late.

165
00:11:02.162 --> 00:11:03.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I still haven't adjusted
to the weather here.

166
00:11:03.955 --> 00:11:05.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It gets so cold at night.

167
00:11:05.456 --> 00:11:07.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's almost curfew.

168
00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:09.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir. We both live right here.

169
00:11:12.338 --> 00:11:13.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good night, then.

170
00:11:15.884 --> 00:11:19.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, one of the advantages
of living in employee housing

171
00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:22.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is that we can continue sharing ideas
even after the workday is over.

172
00:11:23.057 --> 00:11:24.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is that so?
-Yes,

173
00:11:24.309 --> 00:11:27.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I do have a spectacular view
of the river from my living quarters.

174
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:31.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I<i> really</i> have to get to sleep.
Maybe another time.

175
00:11:31.316 --> 00:11:33.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry if I'm making
you uncomfortable.

176
00:11:33.735 --> 00:11:35.945  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're not.

177
00:11:36.029 --> 00:11:37.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, if you get lonely...

178
00:11:37.822 --> 00:11:39.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll let you know.

179
00:11:45.455 --> 00:11:48.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[low, indistinct chatter]

180
00:11:51.294 --> 00:11:53.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[alarm sounds]

181
00:11:56.633 --> 00:11:57.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It wasn't me.

182
00:11:58.009 --> 00:11:59.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

183
00:11:59.344 --> 00:12:02.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not an overload.
It's time for our inoculations.

184
00:12:02.430 --> 00:12:05.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What inoculations?
-They're nothing to worry about.

185
00:12:05.433 --> 00:12:07.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Protection against ambient radiation.

186
00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:09.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't realize that was a problem.

187
00:12:09.854 --> 00:12:12.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not, as long as you're
inoculated regularly.

188
00:12:13.775 --> 00:12:16.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're lucky to have an employer
that concerned about our safety.

189
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:19.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man]
It wasn't that bad.

190
00:12:19.113 --> 00:12:20.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman]
It doesn't bother me.

191
00:12:20.281 --> 00:12:21.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man]
How long did it take to go away?

192
00:12:24.619 --> 00:12:26.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man]
Ten days, two weeks.

193
00:12:32.627 --> 00:12:34.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is something wrong?

194
00:12:34.379 --> 00:12:38.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Forgive me, but I'm--
I'm afraid of injections.

195
00:12:38.383 --> 00:12:40.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I assure you, this is painless.

196
00:12:41.594 --> 00:12:45.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is-- Is there some other method
of administering the medication?

197
00:12:45.556 --> 00:12:47.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, I'm afraid there isn't.

198
00:12:47.892 --> 00:12:48.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very well.

199
00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:56.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No! No! No!

200
00:12:58.569 --> 00:12:59.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're finished.

201
00:12:59.946 --> 00:13:01.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can go back to work.

202
00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:04.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Next.

203
00:13:22.969 --> 00:13:27.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Chakotay]
<i>First Officer's Log, Stardate 54584.3.</i>

204
00:13:27.307 --> 00:13:30.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Ensign Kim, Mr. Neelix,</i>
<i>and I are returning to </i>Voyager

205
00:13:30.351 --> 00:13:32.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>after five days of trading</i>
<i>with the Nar Shaddan.</i>

206
00:13:32.937 --> 00:13:36.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In six years, I've never been
on an away mission

207
00:13:36.190 --> 00:13:37.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
worse than this one.

208
00:13:37.775 --> 00:13:39.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know how you can say that.

209
00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:42.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The cargo hold is crammed
with valuable supplies.

210
00:13:42.905 --> 00:13:48.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And my stomach is crammed
with alien parasites doing backflips.

211
00:13:48.494 --> 00:13:51.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess you shouldn't have drunk
that Falah nectar.

212
00:13:51.289 --> 00:13:53.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You insisted I try it.

213
00:13:53.166 --> 00:13:56.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh! The Nar Shaddan
consider it a delicacy.

214
00:13:56.878 --> 00:13:58.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To refuse would've insulted them.

215
00:13:58.713 --> 00:14:02.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't hear you insisting
that Commander Chakotay try it.

216
00:14:02.592 --> 00:14:05.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Commander Chakotay's
a vegetarian.

217
00:14:06.262 --> 00:14:07.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was made from meat?

218
00:14:07.889 --> 00:14:09.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More like a meat byproduct.

219
00:14:09.682 --> 00:14:12.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[sighs]
I'm going to be sick.

220
00:14:12.310 --> 00:14:14.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not after you drink this.

221
00:14:14.312 --> 00:14:17.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What is it?
<i>-Leola</i> bark tea,

222
00:14:17.398 --> 00:14:19.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to settle even the queasiest
of stomachs.

223
00:14:19.776 --> 00:14:23.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ugh! It smells worse
than the meat nectar.

224
00:14:24.322 --> 00:14:26.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll wait for the Doctor to treat me.

225
00:14:26.991 --> 00:14:28.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At least I'll be sleeping
in my own bed tonight.

226
00:14:28.910 --> 00:14:31.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Chakotay]
<i>Harry, I know you're not feeling well,</i>

227
00:14:31.120 --> 00:14:32.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>but I need you and Neelix up here.</i>

228
00:14:33.081 --> 00:14:34.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On our way.

229
00:14:37.960 --> 00:14:39.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Neelix]
Anything wrong, Commander?

230
00:14:39.962 --> 00:14:42.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're at the rendezvous coordinates,
but there's no sign of<i> Voyager,</i>

231
00:14:43.007 --> 00:14:44.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they're not responding to hails.

232
00:14:44.759 --> 00:14:46.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Start scanning on all frequencies.

233
00:14:46.969 --> 00:14:48.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've got to be out there
somewhere.

234
00:14:50.431 --> 00:14:52.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So much for my own bed.

235
00:14:59.774 --> 00:15:02.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Doctor]
Reinitialize the subspace transponder.

236
00:15:02.318 --> 00:15:05.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Computer, garbled]:
<i>Warning. Main computer is failing.</i>

237
00:15:05.780 --> 00:15:08.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[sighs]
Switch to backup processors.

238
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:11.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[clear]
<i>Main computer stabilized.</i>

239
00:15:11.244 --> 00:15:15.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good. Now let's try this again.

240
00:15:15.415 --> 00:15:18.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Reinitialize
the subspace transponder.

241
00:15:18.084 --> 00:15:19.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Unable to comply.</i>

242
00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:22.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why not?
<i>-Insufficient power.</i>

243
00:15:22.171 --> 00:15:23.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And they say I'm difficult.

244
00:15:24.048 --> 00:15:26.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Reroute power
from the replicator system.

245
00:15:26.634 --> 00:15:28.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-Unable to comply.</i>
<i>-</i>Clarify!

246
00:15:28.636 --> 00:15:31.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Relays to the transponder</i>
<i>are fused.</i>

247
00:15:31.139 --> 00:15:32.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any suggestions?

248
00:15:32.515 --> 00:15:34.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Please restate inquiry.</i>

249
00:15:34.225 --> 00:15:35.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

250
00:15:36.686 --> 00:15:39.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can the power relays be bypassed?

251
00:15:39.522 --> 00:15:40.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Negative.</i>

252
00:15:40.731 --> 00:15:43.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then I suppose I'll have
to replace them by hand.

253
00:15:43.734 --> 00:15:44.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[alarm sounds]

254
00:15:44.944 --> 00:15:46.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Warning. Intruder alert.</i>

255
00:15:46.737 --> 00:15:48.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Where?
<i>-The Bridge.</i>

256
00:15:48.406 --> 00:15:50.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-How many?
<i>-Two humanoids.</i>

257
00:15:50.658 --> 00:15:52.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Can you identify them?
<i>-Negative.</i>

258
00:15:53.035 --> 00:15:56.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Sensor resolution</i>
<i>is below 20 percent.</i>

259
00:16:15.183 --> 00:16:17.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Stop what you're doing
and turn around!

260
00:16:18.394 --> 00:16:20.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kim]
Take it easy, Doc! It's us!

261
00:16:23.399 --> 00:16:25.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's good to see
some friendly faces.

262
00:16:25.651 --> 00:16:28.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For that matter,
it's good to see any faces at all.

263
00:16:28.738 --> 00:16:30.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry I haven't gotten
life support back online yet,

264
00:16:30.865 --> 00:16:33.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but since I've been the only one
aboard, it hasn't been a priority.

265
00:16:33.493 --> 00:16:35.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell happened?

266
00:16:35.328 --> 00:16:37.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We ran into some...problems.

267
00:16:37.163 --> 00:16:39.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can see that. Can you be
a little more specific?

268
00:16:39.832 --> 00:16:40.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course.

269
00:16:43.503 --> 00:16:47.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
About 12 hours after
you left on your away mission,

270
00:16:47.256 --> 00:16:49.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
things started to go wrong.

271
00:16:49.091 --> 00:16:52.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We hit some sort of subspace mine.

272
00:16:55.223 --> 00:16:58.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, transfer the EMH
to the mobile emitter.

273
00:16:59.143 --> 00:17:00.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sick Bay to Bridge.

274
00:17:00.686 --> 00:17:03.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sick Bay to Engineering.
Please respond.

275
00:17:03.105 --> 00:17:05.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It wasn't long before
I was inundated with casualties,

276
00:17:05.816 --> 00:17:08.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
all suffering from
tetryon radiation poisoning.

277
00:17:08.819 --> 00:17:10.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pretty soon, the captain arrived.

278
00:17:11.072 --> 00:17:13.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor, can you treat these people?

279
00:17:13.908 --> 00:17:17.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can stabilize them, but if we can't
contain the radiation...

280
00:17:17.495 --> 00:17:20.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Get everyone to the escape pods,
quickly.

281
00:17:20.122 --> 00:17:21.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not you, Doctor. I need you here.

282
00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:23.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain?

283
00:17:23.084 --> 00:17:26.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, activate the Emergency
Command Hologram.

284
00:17:26.879 --> 00:17:29.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Authorization Janeway Omega 3.

285
00:17:31.384 --> 00:17:33.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Computer]
<i>Command codes transferred.</i>

286
00:17:33.177 --> 00:17:35.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've wanted this chance
for a long time.

287
00:17:35.846 --> 00:17:37.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Now you've got it.
-Aye, Captain.

288
00:17:38.015 --> 00:17:39.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Try to vent the radiation.

289
00:17:39.308 --> 00:17:41.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The rest of us will get out
of the contaminated area

290
00:17:41.143 --> 00:17:43.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and head for the nearest
habitable planet.

291
00:17:43.145 --> 00:17:44.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You need medical care.

292
00:17:44.480 --> 00:17:46.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Unless someone answers
our distress call,

293
00:17:46.107 --> 00:17:47.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we'll have to make due with medkits.

294
00:17:47.692 --> 00:17:50.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll rendezvous as soon
as it's safe to come back on board.

295
00:17:52.822 --> 00:17:54.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take good care of<i> Voyager.</i>

296
00:17:54.907 --> 00:17:57.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can count on me, Captain.

297
00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:04.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Doctor]
<i>The crew abandoned ship,</i>

298
00:18:04.250 --> 00:18:06.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and I began to assess</i>
<i>the damage caused by the mine.</i>

299
00:18:07.003 --> 00:18:10.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But before I could even get</i>
<i>started with the repairs,</i>

300
00:18:10.715 --> 00:18:13.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I got some unexpected company.</i>

301
00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:14.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Computer, report.

302
00:18:14.385 --> 00:18:17.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>An alien vessel has locked</i>
<i>on to </i>Voyager <i>with a tractor beam.</i>

303
00:18:17.763 --> 00:18:18.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Open a channel.

304
00:18:19.015 --> 00:18:21.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is the Federation Starship
<i>Voyager.</i>

305
00:18:21.642 --> 00:18:23.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Disengage your tractor beam.

306
00:18:24.270 --> 00:18:26.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Our scans show no life signs</i>
<i>aboard your vessel.</i>

307
00:18:26.897 --> 00:18:28.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Identify yourself.</i>

308
00:18:28.107 --> 00:18:30.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm the Emergency
Command Hologram.

309
00:18:30.151 --> 00:18:32.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-Hologram.</i>
-That's right.

310
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:33.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now release my ship.

311
00:18:34.071 --> 00:18:36.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Your crew has abandoned it.</i>
<i>It belongs to me now.</i>

312
00:18:36.616 --> 00:18:38.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I beg to differ.

313
00:18:39.452 --> 00:18:43.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, target the vessel's
tractor emitter, and fire.

314
00:18:47.043 --> 00:18:51.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come about, heading 903 mark 6.

315
00:18:52.381 --> 00:18:54.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Engage at warp 2.

316
00:18:55.635 --> 00:18:57.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Computer]
<i>Warp engines are offline.</i>

317
00:18:57.553 --> 00:19:00.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Evasive pattern Beta-4.
Target the vessel's engines.

318
00:19:08.105 --> 00:19:10.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Computer]
<i>Warning. Two vessels approaching,</i>

319
00:19:10.149 --> 00:19:12.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>bearing 336 mark 1.</i>

320
00:19:12.485 --> 00:19:14.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Reverse course, full impulse.

321
00:19:14.445 --> 00:19:16.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I managed to evade
the other two ships

322
00:19:16.947 --> 00:19:18.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and hid inside this nebula.

323
00:19:18.866 --> 00:19:22.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I vented the radiation, repaired
as many systems as I could,

324
00:19:22.453 --> 00:19:26.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but with no help, let's just say
I'm glad you found me.

325
00:19:26.374 --> 00:19:28.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It wasn't easy picking up
your homing signal.

326
00:19:28.709 --> 00:19:31.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I had to encrypt it.
Every time I left the nebula,

327
00:19:31.295 --> 00:19:33.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I detected more ships
searching for me.

328
00:19:33.506 --> 00:19:35.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Chakotay]
Any idea who they are?

329
00:19:35.216 --> 00:19:39.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. But I've analyzed
all of their weapons signatures.

330
00:19:39.887 --> 00:19:42.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They match the subspace mine.

331
00:19:42.973 --> 00:19:46.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was a deliberate attempt
to disable<i> Voyager.</i>

332
00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:49.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good thing you were here.

333
00:19:49.230 --> 00:19:51.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about the rest of the crew?

334
00:19:52.733 --> 00:19:54.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not a word.

335
00:20:11.836 --> 00:20:13.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Make them comfortable.

336
00:20:25.433 --> 00:20:26.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans quietly]

337
00:20:32.064 --> 00:20:34.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're going to treat your injuries.

338
00:20:34.525 --> 00:20:36.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who are you?

339
00:20:36.110 --> 00:20:40.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My name is Dr. Kadan.
You're in a Quarren medical facility.

340
00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:42.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My crew?

341
00:20:42.116 --> 00:20:44.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My understanding
is that they've all been rescued

342
00:20:44.493 --> 00:20:46.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
from their escape pods.

343
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:47.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Treat my people first.

344
00:20:47.663 --> 00:20:50.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everyone will be taken care of.

345
00:20:53.669 --> 00:20:54.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

346
00:21:01.594 --> 00:21:03.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tuvok groans]

347
00:21:03.721 --> 00:21:05.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is that medication?

348
00:21:05.514 --> 00:21:08.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
An antiradiation serum,
perfectly safe.

349
00:21:17.067 --> 00:21:18.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tuvok]
What are you doing?

350
00:21:18.694 --> 00:21:20.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's suffering from
Dysphoria Syndrome.

351
00:21:21.030 --> 00:21:22.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't worry, it's treatable.

352
00:21:22.239 --> 00:21:24.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[electronic whirring]

353
00:21:26.285 --> 00:21:29.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[groans]
Release her immediately.

354
00:21:29.872 --> 00:21:31.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Restrain him.

355
00:21:31.624 --> 00:21:33.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[groans]
Captain!

356
00:21:33.793 --> 00:21:35.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tuvok groans]

357
00:21:36.045 --> 00:21:37.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No! No!

358
00:21:41.133 --> 00:21:44.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[low, indistinct chatter]

359
00:21:48.891 --> 00:21:51.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Excuse me.
-Hi.

360
00:21:51.227 --> 00:21:53.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I believe we know each other.

361
00:21:53.187 --> 00:21:56.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're Tuvok, right? We met
last week at the shift briefing.

362
00:21:56.148 --> 00:21:59.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Before that.
Before we were working here.

363
00:21:59.443 --> 00:22:00.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I don't think so.

364
00:22:00.945 --> 00:22:03.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, we're obviously not
from the same place. [laughs]

365
00:22:03.739 --> 00:22:07.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Still, I believe I know you.

366
00:22:07.201 --> 00:22:09.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
From the hospital, perhaps?

367
00:22:09.245 --> 00:22:11.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What hospital?

368
00:22:11.413 --> 00:22:14.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I am not certain.
We-- We were patients.

369
00:22:14.917 --> 00:22:16.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You must have me confused
with someone else.

370
00:22:16.836 --> 00:22:18.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've never been sick enough
to go to a hospital.

371
00:22:19.004 --> 00:22:20.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry,
I have a lot of work to finish.

372
00:22:21.006 --> 00:22:26.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Please. Try to remember.
It-- It may be important.

373
00:22:26.178 --> 00:22:29.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is there a problem here?
-I think it's just a misunderstanding.

374
00:22:29.682 --> 00:22:30.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tuvok?

375
00:22:33.310 --> 00:22:34.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's right.

376
00:22:34.937 --> 00:22:37.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's, uh...it's a--
it's a misunderstanding.

377
00:22:37.648 --> 00:22:40.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't look well. Maybe
you should go to the infirmary.

378
00:22:40.568 --> 00:22:42.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, no, I'm fine. Fine.

379
00:22:42.903 --> 00:22:45.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, I'll go back to my station.

380
00:22:45.948 --> 00:22:47.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry to have bothered you.

381
00:22:49.660 --> 00:22:52.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What was that all about?
-I'm not sure.

382
00:22:52.580 --> 00:22:54.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Strange man.

383
00:22:54.372 --> 00:22:56.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And a terrible joke teller.

384
00:22:57.543 --> 00:22:59.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So are we having dinner tonight?

385
00:22:59.795 --> 00:23:01.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Again?
-What, you don't like my cooking?

386
00:23:01.881 --> 00:23:05.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-No, it's wonderful. It's just...
-I'm a perfectionist.

387
00:23:05.718 --> 00:23:08.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm going to keep trying
until I make you the perfect meal.

388
00:23:08.762 --> 00:23:10.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And then we stop eating together?

389
00:23:11.015 --> 00:23:14.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll have dinner with you.
On one condition:

390
00:23:15.853 --> 00:23:17.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I make it.

391
00:23:19.607 --> 00:23:22.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I think I can accept those terms.
-Good.

392
00:23:22.902 --> 00:23:24.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now go back to your station

393
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:27.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
before the Efficiency Monitor
catches us fraternizing.

394
00:23:35.706 --> 00:23:36.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[clears throat]

395
00:23:36.957 --> 00:23:38.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I bring you something else?

396
00:23:38.542 --> 00:23:40.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, thank you.

397
00:23:40.586 --> 00:23:42.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't seen you in here before.

398
00:23:42.838 --> 00:23:45.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You probably just didn't notice.

399
00:23:45.257 --> 00:23:47.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'd have noticed.

400
00:23:49.178 --> 00:23:51.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, apparently,
you aren't as observant

401
00:23:51.847 --> 00:23:53.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-as you think you are.
-Oh, really?

402
00:23:53.933 --> 00:23:55.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been coming in here
the same time every day

403
00:23:56.018 --> 00:23:59.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-for the past two weeks.
-Well, that explains it.

404
00:23:59.437 --> 00:24:01.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I usually work nights.

405
00:24:01.148 --> 00:24:02.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me, too.

406
00:24:02.440 --> 00:24:05.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
At the Power Distribution Facility.

407
00:24:05.235 --> 00:24:06.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You see? I am observant.

408
00:24:06.987 --> 00:24:08.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tom.

409
00:24:09.740 --> 00:24:11.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm. I need you for a moment.

410
00:24:12.076 --> 00:24:13.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right there.

411
00:24:16.872 --> 00:24:20.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Listen, you should come back in
when you get a night off.

412
00:24:20.084 --> 00:24:22.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a lot more fun
when there's a crowd.

413
00:24:22.252 --> 00:24:24.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't really like crowds.

414
00:24:24.380 --> 00:24:25.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, then,
maybe we could get together

415
00:24:25.881 --> 00:24:28.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
during the day sometime,
take a walk by the river.

416
00:24:28.634 --> 00:24:30.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I don't think so.
-Why not?

417
00:24:30.219 --> 00:24:33.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I am a very engaging
conversationalist.

418
00:24:35.891 --> 00:24:37.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh.
-Yeah.

419
00:24:38.852 --> 00:24:40.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Still want to get together?

420
00:24:41.605 --> 00:24:42.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're married.

421
00:24:43.065 --> 00:24:44.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

422
00:24:46.068 --> 00:24:47.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

423
00:24:47.319 --> 00:24:49.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Enjoy your day.

424
00:24:58.622 --> 00:25:02.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Chakotay]
<i>First Officer's Log, Stardate 54597.9.</i>

425
00:25:02.918 --> 00:25:05.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>After restoring primary systems,</i>

426
00:25:05.212 --> 00:25:07.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>we've left the nebula</i>
<i>to try to find the crew.</i>

427
00:25:07.715 --> 00:25:09.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Though there's still a lot of damage,</i>

428
00:25:09.925 --> 00:25:11.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>we have been able</i>
<i>to reconfigure sensors</i>

429
00:25:11.677 --> 00:25:13.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to detect subspace mines.</i>

430
00:25:13.387 --> 00:25:16.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Ensign Kim's been running</i>
<i>continuous scans,</i>

431
00:25:16.514 --> 00:25:18.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>but there's still no sign of our people.</i>

432
00:25:18.475 --> 00:25:21.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>On the bright side, the ships</i>
<i>that were searching for us</i>

433
00:25:21.437 --> 00:25:22.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>seem to have given up.</i>

434
00:25:22.563 --> 00:25:26.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>With only four people on board,</i>
<i>repairs are going slowly.</i>

435
00:25:30.279 --> 00:25:33.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Computer] <i>Power to the secondary</i>
<i>propulsion systems</i> has<i> been restored.</i>

436
00:25:34.700 --> 00:25:37.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Kim to the Doctor.</i>
<i>Report to Astrometrics.</i>

437
00:25:37.286 --> 00:25:38.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On my way.

438
00:25:41.290 --> 00:25:42.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any luck?

439
00:25:42.458 --> 00:25:45.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've scanned ships and planets
in 83 systems.

440
00:25:45.419 --> 00:25:49.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No humans, no Vulcans,
no Bolians.

441
00:25:49.465 --> 00:25:50.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe we can increase
the range of the sensors

442
00:25:50.966 --> 00:25:52.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
by tying them into the main deflector.

443
00:25:52.885 --> 00:25:54.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I've already done that.
-Oh.

444
00:25:54.970 --> 00:25:56.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, we can boost resolution by...

445
00:25:56.930 --> 00:25:58.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I appreciate your input, Doc,

446
00:25:58.265 --> 00:26:01.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I didn't call you down here
to help me scan.

447
00:26:01.143 --> 00:26:04.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm still feeling kind of queasy
from that nectar.

448
00:26:04.396 --> 00:26:05.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I treated you days ago.

449
00:26:05.773 --> 00:26:07.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever you did hasn't worked.

450
00:26:07.983 --> 00:26:09.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe all those command
subroutines

451
00:26:10.069 --> 00:26:13.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
are compromising
your medical abilities.

452
00:26:13.530 --> 00:26:17.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe all that sarcasm is
compromising your natural charm.

453
00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:27.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have repaired
the deuterium injectors,

454
00:26:27.169 --> 00:26:29.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
brought secondary propulsion
back online,

455
00:26:29.463 --> 00:26:32.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and soothed Ensign Kim's
upset tummy.

456
00:26:33.050 --> 00:26:35.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Good work.
Why don't you get started

457
00:26:35.469 --> 00:26:37.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
on the ruptured plasma
conduits on Deck 10?

458
00:26:37.930 --> 00:26:39.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can't you take care of those?

459
00:26:41.475 --> 00:26:42.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I beg your pardon?

460
00:26:43.018 --> 00:26:45.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Emergency Command Hologram.

461
00:26:45.354 --> 00:26:47.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doesn't that suggest
my place is here

462
00:26:47.564 --> 00:26:49.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in<i> Voyager's</i> command center?

463
00:26:49.817 --> 00:26:51.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Look, Doc,
I'm impressed with the way

464
00:26:51.318 --> 00:26:53.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you handled yourself
while we were gone.

465
00:26:53.445 --> 00:26:56.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But right now,
we've got to prioritize.

466
00:26:56.573 --> 00:26:58.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-<i>Kim to Chakotay.</i>
<i>-</i>Go ahead.

467
00:26:58.659 --> 00:27:01.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've found them, Commander.
They're on an M-Class planet.

468
00:27:02.037 --> 00:27:04.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At maximum warp, we can be there
in less than three days.

469
00:27:04.665 --> 00:27:06.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Transfer the coordinates
to the helm.

470
00:27:06.792 --> 00:27:08.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be in Astrometrics.

471
00:27:09.795 --> 00:27:12.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doctor,
the Command Center is yours.

472
00:27:14.133 --> 00:27:17.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[elevator doors open and close]

473
00:27:29.189 --> 00:27:30.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mmm, smells good.

474
00:27:30.941 --> 00:27:33.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's only burnt on the outside.

475
00:27:33.110 --> 00:27:35.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your cooking console's
a little temperamental, huh?

476
00:27:35.904 --> 00:27:38.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you try talking to it?

477
00:27:38.115 --> 00:27:40.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once I cut off the charred part,
I'm sure it'll be fine.

478
00:27:41.034 --> 00:27:42.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

479
00:27:55.048 --> 00:27:56.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's good.

480
00:27:56.508 --> 00:27:57.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

481
00:28:01.430 --> 00:28:02.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[utensils clank]
-Let's go.

482
00:28:03.891 --> 00:28:06.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Where?
-I promised you dinner.

483
00:28:06.226 --> 00:28:08.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll just have to get it
somewhere else.

484
00:28:08.770 --> 00:28:10.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait.

485
00:28:10.105 --> 00:28:13.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not really hungry. Are you?

486
00:28:13.483 --> 00:28:14.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

487
00:28:14.902 --> 00:28:16.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's stay here.

488
00:28:29.917 --> 00:28:34.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Chakotay]
<i>First Officer's Log, Stardate 54608.6.</i>

489
00:28:34.588 --> 00:28:36.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We've traced the crew's life signs</i>

490
00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:38.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to a large city</i>
<i>on a planet called Quarra.</i>

491
00:28:38.675 --> 00:28:42.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Unfortunately, the local officials</i>
<i>aren't being very cooperative.</i>

492
00:28:42.930 --> 00:28:45.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I have personally interviewed</i>
<i>several of the individuals</i>

493
00:28:45.849 --> 00:28:48.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>on your crew manifest.</i>
<i>None of them know who you are,</i>

494
00:28:48.894 --> 00:28:51.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>nor have they heard</i>
<i>of a Starship </i>Voyager.

495
00:28:51.897 --> 00:28:53.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like to speak to them myself.

496
00:28:53.774 --> 00:28:55.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>That's not possible.</i>

497
00:28:55.108 --> 00:28:56.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you're telling the truth,

498
00:28:56.860 --> 00:28:59.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you have nothing to lose
by letting us talk to them.

499
00:28:59.196 --> 00:29:02.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Unlike other planets</i>
<i>in this system,</i>

500
00:29:02.532 --> 00:29:06.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>we grant our guest workers</i>
<i>the full protection of our laws.</i>

501
00:29:06.203 --> 00:29:08.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What exactly are you
protecting them from?

502
00:29:08.288 --> 00:29:10.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Unscrupulous individuals</i>

503
00:29:10.290 --> 00:29:12.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>attempting to acquire</i>
<i>skilled laborers.</i>

504
00:29:12.584 --> 00:29:15.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're not trying to acquire laborers.
We're trying to find our friends.

505
00:29:16.004 --> 00:29:18.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Most of your friends</i>
<i>have excellent positions</i>

506
00:29:18.382 --> 00:29:20.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in the Central Power Facility</i>
<i>in the capitol.</i>

507
00:29:20.634 --> 00:29:22.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Why would any of them</i>
<i>want to travel thousands</i>

508
00:29:22.844 --> 00:29:25.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>of light-years to a planet</i>
<i>on the other side of the galaxy</i>

509
00:29:25.472 --> 00:29:28.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>when they have safe,</i>
<i>comfortable lives right here?</i>

510
00:29:28.809 --> 00:29:30.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Because it isn't their home.

511
00:29:30.978 --> 00:29:34.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I suggest you look elsewhere</i>
<i>to increase your labor supply.</i>

512
00:29:34.439 --> 00:29:37.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>And if you attempt</i>
<i>to disturb any of our citizens,</i>

513
00:29:37.359 --> 00:29:39.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>we will respond with force.</i>

514
00:29:41.488 --> 00:29:42.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any luck?

515
00:29:42.614 --> 00:29:44.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's no way to beam them
through the shield grid.

516
00:29:45.033 --> 00:29:46.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take us out of orbit.

517
00:29:46.785 --> 00:29:48.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're not leaving them behind.

518
00:29:48.620 --> 00:29:51.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. But I want these people
to think we are.

519
00:30:09.641 --> 00:30:13.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hope the cooking console's
not being temperamental again.

520
00:30:13.353 --> 00:30:17.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Making a hot drink
is one thing I can do.

521
00:30:19.234 --> 00:30:22.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You're right. It's good.
-I told you.

522
00:30:28.410 --> 00:30:30.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mmm.

523
00:30:30.412 --> 00:30:33.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What's even better
is being here with you.

524
00:30:35.459 --> 00:30:37.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you comfortable?

525
00:30:37.336 --> 00:30:39.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The blanket's nice and warm.

526
00:30:39.671 --> 00:30:42.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, I mean here with me.

527
00:30:47.179 --> 00:30:50.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't remember
being more comfortable...

528
00:30:52.017 --> 00:30:53.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in my life.

529
00:30:56.146 --> 00:30:58.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, I'll take care of it.

530
00:30:58.357 --> 00:31:00.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[clears throat]

531
00:31:00.150 --> 00:31:01.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hi.

532
00:31:03.236 --> 00:31:04.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

533
00:31:04.696 --> 00:31:06.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Listen, I get off work
in a few minutes.

534
00:31:06.948 --> 00:31:08.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought maybe you
and I could go to...

535
00:31:08.575 --> 00:31:10.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't give up, do you?

536
00:31:10.285 --> 00:31:12.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't even know
what I was gonna say.

537
00:31:12.579 --> 00:31:13.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me guess.

538
00:31:14.081 --> 00:31:17.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're going to invite me
to take a walk by the river

539
00:31:17.084 --> 00:31:20.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or maybe to your living quarters
to admire the view.

540
00:31:20.587 --> 00:31:22.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Actually...

541
00:31:22.756 --> 00:31:26.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was going to offer to introduce you
to some people I met.

542
00:31:26.301 --> 00:31:30.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A couple expecting their first baby
in a few weeks.

543
00:31:30.222 --> 00:31:33.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you might want
to get to know some other parents.

544
00:31:33.850 --> 00:31:36.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, swap stories,

545
00:31:36.186 --> 00:31:38.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
maybe even find a playmate
for your baby.

546
00:31:40.607 --> 00:31:41.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If it's a bad idea...

547
00:31:41.942 --> 00:31:44.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

548
00:31:44.194 --> 00:31:45.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, it's nice.

549
00:31:47.197 --> 00:31:49.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Listen, I'm sorry about the other day.

550
00:31:49.366 --> 00:31:51.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm the one
who should be apologizing.

551
00:31:51.326 --> 00:31:52.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I shouldn't have assumed...
-Forget it.

552
00:31:53.036 --> 00:31:55.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, it's rare that I admit I'm wrong,

553
00:31:55.705 --> 00:31:58.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so you might as well take advantage
of it while you can.

554
00:32:01.586 --> 00:32:04.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been hard...

555
00:32:04.214 --> 00:32:06.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
being alone with a baby coming.

556
00:32:06.383 --> 00:32:08.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have a habit
of keeping my guard up.

557
00:32:08.552 --> 00:32:10.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that's understandable.

558
00:32:10.554 --> 00:32:13.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's just...a romantic relationship

559
00:32:13.682 --> 00:32:15.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is really out of the question
for me right now,

560
00:32:15.559 --> 00:32:17.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-and when you started asking...
-How about a friend?

561
00:32:17.102 --> 00:32:18.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

562
00:32:18.562 --> 00:32:22.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you said romance
is out of the question.

563
00:32:22.482 --> 00:32:24.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could you use a friend?

564
00:32:31.533 --> 00:32:33.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens]

565
00:32:33.118 --> 00:32:34.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any progress?

566
00:32:34.619 --> 00:32:36.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've spoken to the captains
of eight vessels

567
00:32:37.080 --> 00:32:39.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that left Quarra
in the last two weeks.

568
00:32:39.374 --> 00:32:41.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No one knew anything
about the crew?

569
00:32:41.376 --> 00:32:44.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. But every one of them asked me
if I was looking for employment.

570
00:32:44.963 --> 00:32:47.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Apparently, there's
a severe labor shortage

571
00:32:47.174 --> 00:32:48.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
throughout this system.

572
00:32:48.467 --> 00:32:50.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a lot of competition
for workers.

573
00:32:50.427 --> 00:32:52.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That ambassador said
most of our people

574
00:32:52.345 --> 00:32:54.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
were working
at the main power facility.

575
00:32:54.514 --> 00:32:57.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wonder if they still have
any positions to fill.

576
00:32:57.309 --> 00:33:00.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can make some inquiries.
Why?

577
00:33:01.688 --> 00:33:03.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because you and I are going
to find ourselves jobs.

578
00:33:03.982 --> 00:33:06.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Reentering orbit
might arouse their suspicion.

579
00:33:06.985 --> 00:33:08.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not if we take my ship.

580
00:33:08.737 --> 00:33:10.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Good idea, Neelix.
-Commander,

581
00:33:10.739 --> 00:33:12.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you've spoken directly
with several government officials.

582
00:33:12.991 --> 00:33:14.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You could be recognized.

583
00:33:14.701 --> 00:33:15.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

584
00:33:15.994 --> 00:33:19.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Isn't reconstructive surgery
one of your specialties?

585
00:33:28.298 --> 00:33:31.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I still say you should've posed
as a Talaxian.

586
00:33:31.718 --> 00:33:33.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'd have made a striking pair.

587
00:33:33.470 --> 00:33:35.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whiskers make me itch.

588
00:33:35.555 --> 00:33:37.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How did it go?

589
00:33:37.474 --> 00:33:39.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As soon as I told the supervisor
our qualifications,

590
00:33:39.809 --> 00:33:41.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
he was eager to hire us.

591
00:33:41.353 --> 00:33:43.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He even helped me get
a docking permit for my ship.

592
00:33:44.064 --> 00:33:46.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll be gainfully employed
by tomorrow morning.

593
00:33:46.525 --> 00:33:49.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Here you go, Doc.
-Give me your hand, Mr. Neelix.

594
00:33:49.236 --> 00:33:50.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's this?

595
00:33:50.445 --> 00:33:51.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kim]
A subdermal transponder.

596
00:33:51.905 --> 00:33:53.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It will allow us
to maintain an open com-link

597
00:33:54.032 --> 00:33:56.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so we can transport you through
the shield grid if there's trouble.

598
00:33:56.701 --> 00:33:59.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hold position
at maximum transporter range.

599
00:33:59.287 --> 00:34:00.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

600
00:34:00.580 --> 00:34:03.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I assumed I'd be in charge
during your absence, Commander.

601
00:34:03.375 --> 00:34:04.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

602
00:34:04.751 --> 00:34:06.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
An Emergency Command Hologram,

603
00:34:06.545 --> 00:34:09.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
programmed with over two million
tactical subroutines,

604
00:34:09.506 --> 00:34:11.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
outranks an Ensign.

605
00:34:11.716 --> 00:34:13.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A few words to the computer,

606
00:34:13.260 --> 00:34:16.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and this Ensign
can delete those subroutines.

607
00:34:16.221 --> 00:34:18.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then you'd be depriving yourself
of a skilled leader

608
00:34:19.057 --> 00:34:20.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for the sake of your ego.

609
00:34:20.433 --> 00:34:22.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh,<i> my</i> ego!
-Gentlemen.

610
00:34:24.062 --> 00:34:25.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Work it out.

611
00:34:25.897 --> 00:34:27.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[both]
Aye, sir.

612
00:34:45.292 --> 00:34:48.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[low, indistinct chatter]

613
00:34:50.630 --> 00:34:53.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Employee 8583.

614
00:34:55.427 --> 00:34:57.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tuvok.

615
00:34:57.429 --> 00:34:59.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
According to my records,
you've neglected to report

616
00:34:59.723 --> 00:35:02.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for your last three inoculations.

617
00:35:03.935 --> 00:35:06.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
These inoculations
are for your protection.

618
00:35:08.648 --> 00:35:11.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A sick worker is not
an efficient worker.

619
00:35:11.735 --> 00:35:13.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Report to the infirmary.

620
00:35:14.070 --> 00:35:15.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Seven of Nine.

621
00:35:16.072 --> 00:35:17.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

622
00:35:17.907 --> 00:35:22.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Seven of Nine.
It's...your designation.

623
00:35:22.245 --> 00:35:24.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My employee number is 8586.

624
00:35:24.998 --> 00:35:27.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Take your hands off me!
Call Security!

625
00:35:34.257 --> 00:35:36.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't believe you are
who you think you are!

626
00:35:38.011 --> 00:35:39.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tuvok]
We don't belong here.

627
00:35:39.638 --> 00:35:41.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We don't belong here!

628
00:35:41.389 --> 00:35:44.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This isn't right!

629
00:35:44.100 --> 00:35:45.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We don't belong here!

630
00:35:55.111 --> 00:35:58.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Qualification Level 3
in microkinetics.

631
00:35:58.531 --> 00:36:00.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You could use some
improvement there.

632
00:36:00.825 --> 00:36:03.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Level 5 in thermionic conversion.

633
00:36:03.536 --> 00:36:04.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good.

634
00:36:04.871 --> 00:36:06.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We lost a thermionic
specialist yesterday.

635
00:36:06.998 --> 00:36:08.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did he find a better job?

636
00:36:08.500 --> 00:36:10.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, health problems.

637
00:36:10.210 --> 00:36:11.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Someone you know?

638
00:36:11.795 --> 00:36:14.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, just...an unusual species.

639
00:36:15.048 --> 00:36:16.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have a diverse workforce.

640
00:36:16.925 --> 00:36:19.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our thermionic converters
operate on a rotating frequency,

641
00:36:20.011 --> 00:36:21.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so they have to be
closely monitored.

642
00:36:21.888 --> 00:36:24.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll be required to report
your readings to the Controller

643
00:36:24.474 --> 00:36:26.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
at regular intervals.

644
00:36:26.685 --> 00:36:28.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any questions?

645
00:36:32.941 --> 00:36:34.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you listening to me?

646
00:36:34.818 --> 00:36:38.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sorry, sir.
I'm just excited to be here.

647
00:36:40.657 --> 00:36:42.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Carry on.

648
00:36:56.881 --> 00:36:59.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Kathryn.
-Yes?

649
00:36:59.676 --> 00:37:01.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's Chakotay.

650
00:37:01.845 --> 00:37:03.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry?

651
00:37:05.390 --> 00:37:06.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm new here.

652
00:37:06.516 --> 00:37:08.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The supervisor said
you would be a good person

653
00:37:08.852 --> 00:37:10.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to speak to if I had any questions.

654
00:37:10.687 --> 00:37:13.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm. What can I help you with?

655
00:37:13.398 --> 00:37:17.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nothing. I just wanted
to introduce myself.

656
00:37:17.485 --> 00:37:20.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh. What did you say
your name was?

657
00:37:20.405 --> 00:37:21.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chakotay.

658
00:37:21.990 --> 00:37:25.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, that's just
what my friends call me.

659
00:37:25.118 --> 00:37:27.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My employment file
lists my given name:

660
00:37:27.954 --> 00:37:30.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Amal Kotay.

661
00:37:30.331 --> 00:37:31.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, whatever your name is,

662
00:37:31.708 --> 00:37:33.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm happy to help you
any way I can.

663
00:37:33.710 --> 00:37:36.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tuvok groans, shudders]

664
00:37:37.756 --> 00:37:39.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. No!

665
00:37:39.382 --> 00:37:42.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're experiencing
a relapse of Dysphoria Syndrome.

666
00:37:42.343 --> 00:37:43.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is going to make you
feel better.

667
00:37:43.928 --> 00:37:46.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get away from me! No, no, please.

668
00:37:47.891 --> 00:37:49.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Losing my job there

669
00:37:49.350 --> 00:37:51.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

670
00:37:52.061 --> 00:37:53.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why is that?

671
00:37:53.313 --> 00:37:55.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, so many rules
and regulations.

672
00:37:55.732 --> 00:37:57.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was like a military operation.

673
00:37:57.817 --> 00:37:58.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know what you mean.

674
00:37:59.068 --> 00:38:01.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"Report here, reroute power there."

675
00:38:01.446 --> 00:38:03.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's almost like serving
aboard a starship.

676
00:38:05.575 --> 00:38:07.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you ever done that?

677
00:38:07.994 --> 00:38:11.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're looking at the former captain
of his own cargo vessel.

678
00:38:11.790 --> 00:38:14.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm, must be quite a life.

679
00:38:14.501 --> 00:38:17.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What about you?
Ever worked on a ship?

680
00:38:17.587 --> 00:38:20.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, no.
Space travel makes me sick.

681
00:38:20.715 --> 00:38:22.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Torres laughing]

682
00:38:23.760 --> 00:38:24.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not lying.

683
00:38:24.886 --> 00:38:28.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Neelix] So, do you know most
of the people that come in here?

684
00:38:28.097 --> 00:38:29.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A lot of them.

685
00:38:29.808 --> 00:38:32.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a great place to work.

686
00:38:32.519 --> 00:38:33.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Seems like it.

687
00:38:33.812 --> 00:38:36.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I could put in a good word
for you to my employer.

688
00:38:36.356 --> 00:38:37.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Chakotay]
Ah, Neelix.

689
00:38:37.482 --> 00:38:39.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was wondering
when you'd get here.

690
00:38:39.609 --> 00:38:42.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Amal Kotay,
this is my new friend Tom Paris.

691
00:38:42.695 --> 00:38:45.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What can I get you?
-That looks good.

692
00:38:47.492 --> 00:38:50.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was assigned
to the primary fusion chamber

693
00:38:50.119 --> 00:38:52.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
along with Mulcahey and Celes.

694
00:38:52.288 --> 00:38:54.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Neither of them recognized me.

695
00:38:54.249 --> 00:38:57.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let me guess.
They really love their jobs.

696
00:38:57.794 --> 00:39:01.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's like they've all been
programmed to be happy here.

697
00:39:01.548 --> 00:39:04.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a safe bet they're not
going to leave willingly.

698
00:39:04.217 --> 00:39:05.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here you go.

699
00:39:05.718 --> 00:39:07.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man]
Look, there's a table over there.

700
00:39:07.095 --> 00:39:09.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

701
00:39:09.138 --> 00:39:10.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man] Hey.
-[woman] Hi.

702
00:39:10.557 --> 00:39:11.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] How are you?

703
00:39:12.058 --> 00:39:14.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hi. How was your first day?
-Not bad.

704
00:39:14.769 --> 00:39:17.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you and your friend
like to join us?

705
00:39:18.147 --> 00:39:19.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That would be nice.

706
00:39:19.357 --> 00:39:22.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Um, actually, I was hoping
we could eat alone tonight.

707
00:39:24.571 --> 00:39:26.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe another time.

708
00:39:29.117 --> 00:39:32.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That was rude.
-I'm sorry. I just, um...

709
00:39:32.161 --> 00:39:34.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's something
I'd like to talk to you about.

710
00:39:38.126 --> 00:39:39.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

711
00:39:39.252 --> 00:39:40.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Bye-bye.
-Thank you for joining us.

712
00:39:41.671 --> 00:39:42.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Paris]
B'Elanna.

713
00:39:44.007 --> 00:39:46.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm due for a break.
I'll walk you to the transport.

714
00:39:47.010 --> 00:39:48.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stop worrying. I'll be fine.

715
00:39:48.845 --> 00:39:51.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's not you that I'm worried about.

716
00:39:52.891 --> 00:39:55.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The baby will be fine, too.

717
00:40:07.238 --> 00:40:09.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what I was thinking is...

718
00:40:11.743 --> 00:40:15.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if we were to combine our resources,

719
00:40:15.872 --> 00:40:18.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we would reduce our expenses.

720
00:40:21.044 --> 00:40:23.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you asking me to move in?

721
00:40:24.631 --> 00:40:26.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

722
00:40:28.593 --> 00:40:30.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know it's impulsive.

723
00:40:30.261 --> 00:40:32.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I...know we haven't known
each other very long,

724
00:40:33.056 --> 00:40:37.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but things are so easy
when we're together.

725
00:40:37.435 --> 00:40:40.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-And I just thought I...
-Okay.

726
00:40:42.273 --> 00:40:43.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

727
00:40:44.901 --> 00:40:47.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe I'm out of my mind...

728
00:40:48.529 --> 00:40:50.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but let's try it.

729
00:40:54.160 --> 00:40:55.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man] I think this is gonna
be a lot of fun, don't you?

730
00:40:55.870 --> 00:40:56.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman]
It's gonna be great. You'll see.

731
00:40:57.038 --> 00:40:58.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Yeah.
-Yeah, they're waiting for us.

732
00:40:58.498 --> 00:41:00.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on, we got to go, all right?

733
00:41:00.708 --> 00:41:03.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[low, indistinct chatter]

734
00:41:05.964 --> 00:41:08.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[gasps]
-Oh, excuse me.

735
00:41:08.841 --> 00:41:12.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was my fault.
I should watch where I'm going.

736
00:41:12.887 --> 00:41:14.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
B'Elanna?

737
00:41:14.472 --> 00:41:17.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How do you know my name?

738
00:41:17.100 --> 00:41:19.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if I told you
we were old friends?

739
00:41:21.521 --> 00:41:23.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a ridiculous statement.

740
00:41:24.607 --> 00:41:26.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know it sounds strange,
but I can prove it to you.

741
00:41:26.943 --> 00:41:29.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, I'm sorry, but I'm late for work.

742
00:41:29.445 --> 00:41:31.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Let go of me!
-I'm not going to hurt you.

743
00:41:31.781 --> 00:41:33.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

744
00:41:33.658 --> 00:41:35.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[screams] Security, help!

745
00:41:35.576 --> 00:41:37.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chakotay to<i> Voyager.</i>
We've got B'Elanna.

746
00:41:37.870 --> 00:41:40.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Lock on to Neelix's signal,</i>
<i>and transport them to Sick Bay.</i>

747
00:41:40.790 --> 00:41:43.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Acknowledged.
-Help me!

748
00:41:44.377 --> 00:41:45.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let her go!

749
00:41:49.465 --> 00:41:51.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stop!

750
00:41:51.134 --> 00:41:53.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Harry, I need
an emergency transport<i> now!</i>

751
00:41:54.762 --> 00:41:56.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sorry, Commander,
we're under attack.

752
00:41:56.806 --> 00:41:58.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had to raise shields.

753
00:42:02.061 --> 00:42:05.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[grunting]
No, leave me alone!

754
00:42:05.648 --> 00:42:07.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're friends.
We're trying to help you.

755
00:42:07.734 --> 00:42:09.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, don't touch me!

756
00:42:13.156 --> 00:42:16.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[electronic whirring]

757
00:42:27.962 --> 00:42:29.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

758
00:42:40.475 --> 00:42:42.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He turned into the accessway.

759
00:42:42.643 --> 00:42:44.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll call for reinforcements.

760
00:42:58.701 --> 00:43:00.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I think he went in there!

761
00:43:00.369 --> 00:43:02.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Be careful! He might be armed!

